OL,3,CHancock: Moving patients from
OL,4,Chospitals to care homes was least-
OL,5,Cworst decision
OL,7,FFormer Health Secretary Matt Hancock
OL,8,Fhas told the Covid-19 inquiry that
OL,9,Fdischarging patients from hospital
OL,10,Finto care homes during the pandemic
OL,11,Fwas the "least worst" move at the time.
OL,13,FA total of 46,000 care home residents
OL,14,Fdied from Covid 19 between March 2020
OL,15,Fand July 2022.
OL,17,FMr Hancock, who was responsible for
OL,18,Fadult care services in England during
OL,19,Fthat period, was giving evidence to
OL,20,Fthe Covid-19 inquiry for the seventh
OL,21,Ftime.
