OL,3,CHancock: Moving patients from
OL,4,Chospitals to care homes was least-
OL,5,Cworst decision
OL,7,FMr Hancock told the inquiry, hospitals
OL,8,Fwere overwhelmed and that there was a
OL,9,F"high likelihood" the situation would
OL,10,Fhave been worse if people had stayed
OL,11,Fin hospital.
OL,13,FThe High Court ruled in 2022 that
OL,14,Fgovernment policies on discharging
OL,15,Fhospital patients into care homes at
OL,16,Fthe start of the pandemic were
OL,17,F"unlawful".
OL,19,FHe said they tried to put a
OL,20,F"protective ring" around care homes.
