OL,3,CHancock: Moving patients from
OL,4,Chospitals to care homes was least-
OL,5,Cworst decision
OL,7,FBut the inquiry heard many care homes
OL,8,Fdid not have isolation facilities and
OL,9,FMr Hancock recommended legislation
OL,10,Fchanges to ensure all homes have such
OL,11,Ffacilities now, as well as a constant
OL,12,Fstock of personal protective equipment
OL,13,F(PPE).
OL,15,FHe also told the inquiry that pandemic
OL,16,Fcontingency plans, prepared by local
OL,17,Fauthorities for adult social care, had
OL,18,Fbeen "as good as useless" at the time,
OL,19,Fand described a "hodgepodge of
OL,20,Faccountability" between local councils
OL,21,Fand government departments.
